[http://www.gams.com GAMS] is a high-level modeling environment for mathematical optimization. GAMS can employ GLPK as its underlying solver by virtue of the [http://www.coin-or.org COIN-OR] [http://projects.coin-or.org/GAMSlinks GAMSlinks] initiative. This feature relies on the COIN-OR Osi project, discussed [[GLPK/Third-party_API_wrappers#COIN-OR_Open_solver_interface_(Osi) |here]] (with accompanying caveats).

GAMS and GLPK can also swap models at a low level using one of several common '''problem specification formats''', including the [[w:MPS_(format)|MPS]] format.  The GLPK [[GLPK/Interoperability|interoperability page]] provides more information.

